Chris Hani Baragwanath Hospital recorded 287 deaths between January and October this year, compared to 466 during the same period last year. JOHANNESBURG The Gauteng Health Department says it s pleased with the progress it s made in reducing neonatal deaths at the Chris Hani Baragwanath Hospital in Soweto, after recording 287 deaths between January and October this year, compared to 466 during the same period last year.The hospital serves a large community and delivers around 20,000 deliveries yearly. The department has attributed the reduction to various interventions that have been implemented at the hospital, including the addition of a second 24 hour theatre. It also says the causes of deaths vary case by case but they emanate from three main conditions such as congenital abnormalities, prematurity infection and asphyxia. The department s Steve Mabona says: As a department we are delighted to announce that there s a reduction of the number of neonatal infants that pass on at the Chris Hani Baragwanath Hospital. (Edited by Winnie Theletsane)